WEBVTT

00:01.210 --> 00:03.128
[ Fanfare plays on cellphone ]

00:03.128 --> 00:05.464
[ All chanting "Lulu!" ]

00:08.592 --> 00:10.636
[ Cellphone beeps,
fanfare and chanting stops ]

00:10.636 --> 00:11.637
You believe it?

00:11.637 --> 00:13.639
She scored five goals.

00:13.639 --> 00:16.183
Well, to be fair,
it was the goalie's nap time.

00:17.601 --> 00:19.811
Is this what pride
feels like?

00:19.811 --> 00:21.855
I've never
felt it before.

00:21.855 --> 00:23.857
[ Knock on door ]

00:27.319 --> 00:29.404
You left me
in the car.

00:31.323 --> 00:33.784
Honey, I'm so sorry.

00:33.784 --> 00:36.161
It's okay.
You also left your keys.

00:36.161 --> 00:39.915
Wait. You were in the car
alone with the ‐‐

00:39.915 --> 00:41.041
Yeah, she moved it.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.626
What?!
I'm kidding.

00:42.626 --> 00:43.752
I'm kidding.
I'm kidding. I'm just kidding.

00:43.752 --> 00:45.462
I've got to go
change Lulu.

00:45.462 --> 00:47.297
She got so excited
about the victory,

00:47.297 --> 00:49.675
she literally
pooped herself.

00:51.093 --> 00:52.469
Whatcha doing?

00:52.469 --> 00:53.971
My puzzle game.

00:53.971 --> 00:55.264
Mm.

00:55.264 --> 00:57.349
You know, Emily, there's still
time to sign you up

00:57.349 --> 00:59.434
if you want to play soccer
like your sister.

00:59.434 --> 01:01.019
I don't want to
kick the ball.

01:01.019 --> 01:03.105
I feel like
I'm hurting it.

01:05.566 --> 01:07.150
[ Sighs ]
We've got to get her

01:07.150 --> 01:08.694
into something besides
that puzzle game.

01:08.694 --> 01:10.654
Yeah.
She's a sweet kid.

01:10.654 --> 01:12.906
The world
is gonna destroy her.

01:12.906 --> 01:14.157
[ Door opens ]

01:16.368 --> 01:17.536
Oh, Jo,

01:17.536 --> 01:20.831
I notice you lose your keys
a lot.

01:20.831 --> 01:21.999
Do I?

01:21.999 --> 01:23.292
Yes, you do.

01:23.292 --> 01:26.295
That's why I thought
you'd like my new purse.

01:26.295 --> 01:27.796
It has a special
key pocket.

01:27.796 --> 01:29.131
Uh‐huh.

01:29.131 --> 01:30.882
And a‐a holder
for your phone.

01:30.882 --> 01:32.593
Neat.

01:32.593 --> 01:37.806
And I call this little
special pouch "the gum zone."

01:37.806 --> 01:39.391
That's really great.

01:39.391 --> 01:40.475
Don't you just love it?

01:40.475 --> 01:42.352
Careful.

01:45.397 --> 01:46.815
I‐I do.

01:46.815 --> 01:48.650
I ‐‐ I do just love it.

01:48.650 --> 01:50.027
I knew you'd love it.

01:50.027 --> 01:51.820
So I got one for you,
too!

01:53.739 --> 01:55.657
Yay.
[ Laughs ]

01:55.657 --> 01:57.492
Now you won't be
a hot mess.

01:57.492 --> 01:59.578
You'll just be hot.

01:59.578 --> 02:00.704
Like me.

02:12.007 --> 02:14.509
We have to do something
about her gifts.

02:14.509 --> 02:16.637
This cannot be my purse.

02:16.637 --> 02:18.930
It looks like
a giant gorilla testicle.

02:22.809 --> 02:26.021
Quick impression ‐‐
me, 10 years ago.

02:32.152 --> 02:41.161
♪♪

02:42.496 --> 02:44.331
[ Sighs ]

02:45.999 --> 02:48.502
I gave this bag a shot,
but I can't.

02:48.502 --> 02:51.213
A hawk tried to
steal it from me.

02:55.133 --> 02:56.510
You know,
before I met you,

02:56.510 --> 02:59.012
I never changed my sheets,
and it was fine.

03:01.765 --> 03:03.975
You know [Sighs]
if your mom would stop

03:03.975 --> 03:06.061
spending all her money
on terrible gifts,

03:06.061 --> 03:08.814
maybe she could, like,
chip in on groceries instead.

03:08.814 --> 03:11.024
I know. She keeps eating
all the string cheese.

03:11.024 --> 03:12.818
[ Emily and Lulu screaming ]

03:12.818 --> 03:14.861
Emily: Give it to me!
Lulu: My trophy!

03:14.861 --> 03:16.780
Your turn.

03:18.740 --> 03:20.867
Hey, what's going on?

03:20.867 --> 03:23.453
Lulu wouldn't
give me her trophy.

03:23.453 --> 03:25.414
Oh, Emily.

03:25.414 --> 03:28.166
You know the best way
to get a trophy?

03:28.166 --> 03:32.129
Lulu gives me hers?

03:34.965 --> 03:39.636
No, no, you earn one by
playing soccer, like Lulu.

03:39.636 --> 03:41.763
Nah. I don't want to
lose my weekends.

03:43.640 --> 03:46.601
You know, you don't have to
play a whole season.

03:46.601 --> 03:48.854
Your Tío Chuy
has a soccer clinic,

03:48.854 --> 03:50.355
and if you try it
for a day,

03:50.355 --> 03:52.065
you get
a participation trophy.

03:52.065 --> 03:53.942
Just a day?

03:53.942 --> 03:56.486
And do you promise
I'll get a trophy?

03:56.486 --> 03:58.822
Yes.
Fine.

04:03.034 --> 04:04.494
Are we making
a mistake here?

04:04.494 --> 04:06.204
Definitely, but what are you
talking about?

04:10.959 --> 04:13.795
I don't want to bribe Emily
into playing sports.

04:13.795 --> 04:16.465
I mean, why doesn't she
just like them like we did?

04:16.465 --> 04:19.593
Babe, you remember that moment
in the hospital

04:19.593 --> 04:21.761
when we were alone
with that other couple?

04:21.761 --> 04:23.847
Yeah.

04:23.847 --> 04:25.307
Did we take the right kid?

04:26.892 --> 04:30.145
♪♪

04:30.145 --> 04:32.981
Alright,
my superstar niece is here.

04:32.981 --> 04:34.816
And Emily.

04:34.816 --> 04:36.193
Hi, Tío Chuy.

04:36.193 --> 04:37.819
Why don't you go
run a few suicides,

04:37.819 --> 04:39.154
and we'll start
in a minute?

04:40.989 --> 04:42.449
[ Sighs ]
So, Chuy,

04:42.449 --> 04:45.702
it took a lot of encouragement
to get Emily here today, so...

04:45.702 --> 04:47.662
Ah, you don't know how to
motivate your kid,

04:47.662 --> 04:49.998
so you need me to step in
and save your family.

04:49.998 --> 04:51.333
I got it.

04:51.333 --> 04:53.627
Yep, that's exactly
what we were gonna say.

04:54.628 --> 04:57.088
Hey, Jo,
I love that purse.

04:57.088 --> 04:58.799
Okay. That's it.
It's gone.

05:00.467 --> 05:03.470
Kids, you probably
know who I am.

05:03.470 --> 05:06.348
Local soccer legend,
Chuy Rodriguez.

05:06.348 --> 05:07.766
Chh, chh!
[ Pops lips ]

05:07.766 --> 05:09.351
[ Exhales sharply ]

05:09.351 --> 05:11.353
[ Chuckles ]

05:11.353 --> 05:13.480
Today it is my honor

05:13.480 --> 05:16.608
to introduce you
to the most beautiful game ‐‐

05:16.608 --> 05:17.984
soccer.

05:17.984 --> 05:20.320
And then
you'll all get trophies.

05:20.320 --> 05:22.989
Yay!
Yay!
Yay!
Yay!

05:22.989 --> 05:25.450
Soccer has just a few
simple rules.

05:25.450 --> 05:28.036
Rule number one ‐‐
you can only use your feet.

05:28.036 --> 05:29.037
No hands.

05:29.037 --> 05:30.622
Okay, little early
for questions,

05:30.622 --> 05:31.832
but, uh,
what's up, Emily?

05:31.832 --> 05:33.667
Why can't we use
our hands?

05:33.667 --> 05:35.377
Well, because, uh,
soccer's been around

05:35.377 --> 05:37.170
for thousands of years,

05:37.170 --> 05:38.922
and no one's ever
used their hands.

05:41.174 --> 05:42.217
Yes?

05:42.217 --> 05:44.886
Did people used to
not have hands?

05:44.886 --> 05:46.137
What?

05:46.137 --> 05:48.515
No. No, no, no. People ‐‐
People had hands.

05:48.515 --> 05:51.017
Then why did
they hate them?

05:51.017 --> 05:54.020
Let's not talk
about hands.

05:54.020 --> 05:55.981
If you don't want to
talk about hands,

05:55.981 --> 05:58.191
then why did you
bring it up?

05:58.191 --> 06:01.486
Okay, change of plans.

06:01.486 --> 06:03.405
Uh, we're gonna do
some sprints.

06:03.405 --> 06:05.866
Okay, now, everybody
run between the cones.

06:05.866 --> 06:07.826
[ Blows whistle ]

06:12.163 --> 06:14.916
Hey, uh...

06:14.916 --> 06:16.084
What are you doing?

06:16.084 --> 06:19.004
I'm not allowed
to use my hands.

06:19.004 --> 06:22.132
Well, you ‐‐ you can use
your hands for that.

06:22.132 --> 06:25.385
This is the most confusing thing
that's ever happened to me.

06:26.636 --> 06:27.846
Me, too.

06:27.846 --> 06:31.641
♪♪

06:31.641 --> 06:34.436
[ Groans ]

06:34.436 --> 06:37.314
Hey, uh,
where's my mom's purse?

06:37.314 --> 06:39.149
[ Smacks lips ]
About that.

06:39.149 --> 06:41.318
Oh, no.

06:41.318 --> 06:43.653
You know I love your mom.

06:43.653 --> 06:44.988
You do?

06:44.988 --> 06:47.032
Of course.

06:47.032 --> 06:48.074
[ Scoffs ]

06:48.074 --> 06:51.077
But a purse is
enormously personal.

06:51.077 --> 06:53.163
That's why
they call it a purse.

06:53.163 --> 06:54.998
Hmm. Really?

06:54.998 --> 06:56.958
No.

06:56.958 --> 06:59.169
Oh, my God, babe.
[ Chuckles ]

06:59.169 --> 07:01.254
Look, hon,
I know it's a lot to ask,

07:01.254 --> 07:03.548
but you don't have to use it
the rest of your life.

07:03.548 --> 07:05.258
Just the rest of hers.

07:05.258 --> 07:06.593
You don't get it.

07:06.593 --> 07:08.928
It's different for you, because
you actually like her gifts.

07:08.928 --> 07:10.847
Pbht! What?

07:10.847 --> 07:12.182
No, I don't.

07:13.141 --> 07:14.309
You don't?

07:14.309 --> 07:15.310
No.

07:15.310 --> 07:16.603
Every birthday
since I was 10,

07:16.603 --> 07:17.937
she's given me
a plaid shirt.

07:17.937 --> 07:19.522
You think I like
plaid shirts?

07:19.522 --> 07:20.982
Yes.

07:20.982 --> 07:22.651
You wear one every day.

07:22.651 --> 07:25.153
This is like
a prison to me.

07:25.153 --> 07:28.490
I want to wear
Hawaiian shirts.

07:28.490 --> 07:31.326
Hawaiian shirts!

07:31.326 --> 07:33.703
That sounds very doable.

07:33.703 --> 07:35.497
Why don't you
just talk to her?

07:35.497 --> 07:37.499
Oh, you don't think
I've tried?

07:37.499 --> 07:39.542
Once, in 2005,
I started to,

07:39.542 --> 07:42.962
and she looked at me like that
possum you ran over last year.

07:44.339 --> 07:47.467
[ Whimpers ]
Blblblbl!

07:47.467 --> 07:50.345
Don't ever bring him up.

07:52.222 --> 07:55.100
Okay, look,
i‐i‐in your family,

07:55.100 --> 07:56.810
if you don't like something,
you just tell each other, right?

07:56.810 --> 07:57.769
Yeah.

07:57.769 --> 07:59.020
Well, that's not
how we do it.

07:59.020 --> 08:00.355
[ Scoffs ]

08:00.355 --> 08:02.941
What do you think is gonna
happen if you're honest?

08:02.941 --> 08:05.276
It would
destroy the system.
What system?

08:05.276 --> 08:07.570
The system of never, ever
saying what you think

08:07.570 --> 08:10.657
to avoid releasing a lifetime of
unexpressed emotions.

08:10.657 --> 08:12.701
You're crazy.

08:12.701 --> 08:13.868
Why don't we
go get the kids?

08:13.868 --> 08:15.495
Okay, sure.
[ Sniffs ]

08:15.495 --> 08:17.163
Where are they?

08:17.163 --> 08:19.457
♪♪

08:19.457 --> 08:21.793
Congratulations.

08:21.793 --> 08:24.170
I know participation trophies
are stupid, but ‐‐

08:24.170 --> 08:26.423
So stupid.

08:26.423 --> 08:28.717
...I'm excited
for Emily to get one.

08:28.717 --> 08:29.718
Me too.
Yeah.

08:29.718 --> 08:31.136
She needs a win.

08:31.136 --> 08:33.763
I mean, even just getting her
to participate

08:33.763 --> 08:35.265
was a huge
accomplishment.

08:35.265 --> 08:37.600
Yeah, they should give us
a trophy.

08:37.600 --> 08:39.602
[ Applause ]

08:39.602 --> 08:42.939
Mom, Dad,

08:42.939 --> 08:45.442
I didn't get a trophy.

08:45.442 --> 08:46.526
What?

08:46.526 --> 08:49.362
Tío Chuy
didn't give me one.

08:51.406 --> 08:53.283
Chuy, what the [bleep]

08:53.283 --> 08:56.244
You said every kid
gets a trophy!

08:56.244 --> 08:59.164
If they participate.
Emily did not.

08:59.164 --> 09:00.290
What are you talking about?

09:00.290 --> 09:02.208
Emily didn't
kick the ball once.

09:02.208 --> 09:05.795
She spent six hours trying to
eat a sandwich with her foot.

09:05.795 --> 09:08.965
Well, that's a new
level of weird.

09:08.965 --> 09:10.967
Okay, Chuy,
but she was here,

09:10.967 --> 09:12.635
so Emily should get
a damn trophy.

09:12.635 --> 09:17.849
Jo, attendance is not
the same as participation.

09:17.849 --> 09:19.642
If I give her one,

09:19.642 --> 09:22.687
then a participation trophy
means nothing.

09:22.687 --> 09:25.356
Exactly.
It's just a piece of plastic.

09:25.356 --> 09:27.567
Chuy, come on.

09:27.567 --> 09:30.153
She's been refusing
to play sports for years.

09:30.153 --> 09:31.821
Look, we finally
got her here, okay?

09:31.821 --> 09:33.323
If Emily doesn't
get a trophy today,

09:33.323 --> 09:35.158
I‐I don't think she's ever gonna
try sports again.

09:35.158 --> 09:37.619
So, you guys screw up
for six years,

09:37.619 --> 09:39.996
and you expect me
to fix it in six hours?

09:39.996 --> 09:42.665
That's exactly what you said
you were gonna do.

09:43.958 --> 09:45.794
As much as I love
my niece,

09:45.794 --> 09:47.170
when I get to
the pearly gates,

09:47.170 --> 09:48.296
I don't want
the big guy saying,

09:48.296 --> 09:51.132
"Why did you lie
and say Emily participated?

09:51.132 --> 09:55.303
I expected more from local
soccer legend Chuy Rodriguez."

10:00.975 --> 10:03.520
I'm gonna destroy him
on Yelp.

10:08.440 --> 10:09.608
[ Sighs ]

10:09.608 --> 10:12.152
You promised
if I went to the stupid thing,

10:12.152 --> 10:14.404
I would get a trophy.

10:15.364 --> 10:17.699
Yeah, but you didn't
actually play soccer.

10:17.699 --> 10:18.784
Who cares?

10:18.784 --> 10:20.661
I just want a trophy.

10:20.661 --> 10:22.788
[ Sighs ]

10:22.788 --> 10:24.831
Emily, if Daddy or I
went to work

10:24.831 --> 10:26.124
and didn't do anything,

10:26.124 --> 10:27.209
do you think
we'd still get paid?

10:27.209 --> 10:29.294
Mm, it's kind of
a gray area for me.

10:30.921 --> 10:34.216
Yeah, you know,
government work.

10:35.342 --> 10:38.261
You're always
changing the rules.

10:39.638 --> 10:41.765
[ Footsteps fade ]

10:43.058 --> 10:44.184
Before kids,

10:44.184 --> 10:46.895
did you ever imagine
having a problem like this?

10:46.895 --> 10:49.231
[ Scoffs ] "I don't want to
eat my broccoli"?

10:49.231 --> 10:50.899
Sure.

10:50.899 --> 10:53.694
"Not gonna do my homework."
Heard of that.

10:53.694 --> 10:54.903
"I don't like fun."

10:56.697 --> 10:58.323
It's not something
they tell you about.

10:58.323 --> 11:00.409
The only thing she ever does
without complaining

11:00.409 --> 11:01.785
is that puzzle game.
I know.

11:01.785 --> 11:04.037
I kept thinking this was gonna
get better as she got older.

11:04.037 --> 11:06.123
But now she is older,
and it's not better.

11:06.123 --> 11:09.793
We've tried so many
activities ‐‐ piano, ballet.

11:09.793 --> 11:12.838
She wouldn't even pretend
to have a job in improv.

11:12.838 --> 11:15.632
[ Chuckling ] Oh.
I remember that.

11:15.632 --> 11:16.925
She kept saying,
"I'm unemployed."

11:16.925 --> 11:18.885
[ Laughs ]

11:18.885 --> 11:21.179
I don't know. We ‐‐
We can't give up on her.

11:21.179 --> 11:24.224
We j‐‐ We have to find a way to
get her interested in something.

11:25.934 --> 11:27.185
What are you
talking about?

11:27.185 --> 11:28.395
We were just saying
that we need to get Emily

11:28.395 --> 11:29.896
interested in something.

11:29.896 --> 11:33.650
Oh, you need to get Emily
interested in something.

11:33.650 --> 11:36.653
Right, yes,
I‐I just said that.

11:36.653 --> 11:39.489
But, hey, you know,
since we're all talking...

11:39.489 --> 11:40.824
[ Chuckles ]

11:40.824 --> 11:42.576
Yes?

11:42.576 --> 11:44.786
The purse you got me ‐‐
very thoughtful.

11:44.786 --> 11:46.621
Oh, thank you.

11:47.748 --> 11:48.915
Yes.

11:48.915 --> 11:51.084
However, a purse...

12:00.469 --> 12:01.970
I...

12:05.474 --> 12:07.184
You know ‐‐
Jo lost the purse.

12:07.184 --> 12:10.270
Yes, yes! Yes.
It's so crazy.

12:10.270 --> 12:12.272
You bought me the purse so that
I wouldn't lose my keys,

12:12.272 --> 12:14.608
and then I lost the purse
that was supposed to
help me not lose my keys.

12:14.608 --> 12:17.110
I guess ‐‐ I guess I need
a purse for my purse.

12:17.110 --> 12:18.236
[ Laughs ]

12:19.780 --> 12:20.989
Okay.

12:23.116 --> 12:24.826
[ Door opens ]

12:24.826 --> 12:26.870
God.
I couldn't do it.

12:26.870 --> 12:28.705
I cou‐‐ You were right.

12:28.705 --> 12:31.124
Her whole eye was pupil.

12:32.584 --> 12:35.420
Couldn't just use the purse
for the rest of her life, huh?

12:35.420 --> 12:37.631
Alright,
what happens now?

12:40.383 --> 12:42.511
You're gonna
bury that purse.

12:46.264 --> 12:49.559
[ Fanfare plays on cellphone ]

12:49.559 --> 12:50.977
Okay, Emily.

12:50.977 --> 12:52.771
[ Cellphone beeps,
fanfare stops ]
Open your eyes.

12:52.771 --> 12:56.483
Welcome to
the Olympics of You.

12:56.483 --> 12:59.152
The what of me?

13:00.112 --> 13:01.780
Olympics. Remember?

13:01.780 --> 13:04.157
We watched the summer ones
like three years ago?

13:04.157 --> 13:05.867
I was 3.

13:05.867 --> 13:09.246
Do you remember
when you were 3?

13:09.246 --> 13:12.290
No, but I've had
a lot of drinks.

13:13.917 --> 13:15.752
Look,
i‐in the Olympics,

13:15.752 --> 13:19.172
people participate
in a bunch of different sports.

13:19.172 --> 13:21.174
And you can earn
this trophy

13:21.174 --> 13:24.219
if you try any of the sports
on this lawn.

13:24.219 --> 13:26.513
Take your time, honey.

13:26.513 --> 13:29.224
See what speaks
to you.

13:31.685 --> 13:34.980
Hello?

13:34.980 --> 13:37.023
It's not saying anything.

13:37.023 --> 13:39.734
Okay, that ‐‐ No, that's just
a figure of speech.

13:39.734 --> 13:41.695
Here. How does the ball
feel in your hands?

13:41.695 --> 13:43.655
This one's too hard.

13:46.324 --> 13:47.909
This one's too soft.

13:49.870 --> 13:52.163
This one's gonna be
just right.

13:52.163 --> 13:53.874
I hate this one!

13:56.585 --> 13:58.753
[ Fanfare plays ]

14:01.548 --> 14:02.549
Oh!

14:02.549 --> 14:03.967
Basket.

14:03.967 --> 14:05.635
Great job, Lulu!

14:06.887 --> 14:08.972
See? It's not hard.

14:08.972 --> 14:10.140
Lulu did it.

14:14.060 --> 14:17.188
If Lulu can do it,
I‐I bet you can, too.

14:17.188 --> 14:20.650
You like Lulu
better than me.

14:31.161 --> 14:32.162
Hey, Lulu.

14:33.330 --> 14:34.539
Read the room.

14:42.172 --> 14:43.798
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

14:44.925 --> 14:47.344
Just draw a dagger
through my heart.

14:47.344 --> 14:49.387
What color?

14:51.431 --> 14:54.100
Hey, Em,
can we talk to you?

14:56.311 --> 14:58.897
Hey, we don't
like Lulu better than you.

14:58.897 --> 15:01.691
Yeah, there are no favorites
in this family, okay?

15:01.691 --> 15:02.943
I mean, you know,
it's like Mom and me.

15:02.943 --> 15:04.277
You don't have a favorite,
right?

15:04.277 --> 15:05.820
Yeah, I do. It's Mom.
Don't answer tha‐‐

15:05.820 --> 15:09.282
It was a hypothetical.
You ‐‐

15:09.282 --> 15:11.242
Look, we're just trying
to get you interested

15:11.242 --> 15:13.787
in something other than
your puzzle game.

15:13.787 --> 15:15.330
I love that game.

15:15.330 --> 15:16.456
We know.

15:16.456 --> 15:19.000
There's just
a lot more to life.

15:19.000 --> 15:21.419
Than doing what you love?

15:27.133 --> 15:28.301
Yes.

15:29.970 --> 15:31.972
The real lesson here is

15:31.972 --> 15:35.016
that there's a whole,
big world out there, baby,

15:35.016 --> 15:36.893
and you should
try new things.

15:36.893 --> 15:40.313
No, thanks. I just want to
lay in bed and play my game.

15:40.313 --> 15:41.356
Okay.

15:41.356 --> 15:44.150
Then the real,
real lesson here

15:44.150 --> 15:46.027
is that no matter what,

15:46.027 --> 15:48.446
you're special,
and we love you, okay?

15:48.446 --> 15:50.865
I love you, too.

15:54.995 --> 15:59.124
Even though Lulu has two
trophies and I have none.

16:01.042 --> 16:03.962
Oh, God. She's doing
your mom's pupil thing.

16:05.797 --> 16:09.134
You know what?
Hold that thought.

16:11.553 --> 16:12.554
Here.

16:12.554 --> 16:15.140
This is for being
a great kid.

16:15.140 --> 16:17.809
[ Gasps ]

16:17.809 --> 16:19.019
Okay, we're done here.

16:19.019 --> 16:21.146
Thank you. Bye.
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

16:21.146 --> 16:23.273
Thank you. Bye‐bye‐bye.
Bye‐bye‐bye‐bye.

16:23.273 --> 16:25.150
Thank you,
thank you, thank you.

16:28.111 --> 16:30.113
Did we just get played?

16:31.448 --> 16:34.367
Well, she's not doing sports,
she didn't learn anything,

16:34.367 --> 16:36.995
we gave her a trophy,
and got kicked out of her room.

16:36.995 --> 16:38.204
So, yeah.

16:41.499 --> 16:42.959
Oh, Jo.
Jo: Mm.

16:42.959 --> 16:45.378
Would you get me
a diet soda from the fridge?

16:45.378 --> 16:47.130
Sure.
Thanks.

16:48.465 --> 16:50.341
Aah!

16:53.887 --> 16:55.555
Something wrong, Jo?

16:55.555 --> 16:57.348
You look as though
you've seen a ghost.

17:01.352 --> 17:03.104
The purse.
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:03.104 --> 17:04.814
You found it.

17:04.814 --> 17:07.650
How?

17:07.650 --> 17:09.944
I put a tracking tile
in it.

17:09.944 --> 17:12.405
Well, you do lose things

17:12.405 --> 17:14.407
and you said
you liked it a lot,

17:14.407 --> 17:17.660
and I found it
in a bag in a hole.

17:20.914 --> 17:22.874
Oh, Bill,

17:22.874 --> 17:24.626
do you know
anything about this?

17:24.626 --> 17:26.753
I told her not to,
Mommy.

17:28.296 --> 17:29.464
Nice.

17:29.464 --> 17:31.132
It seems
we need to talk.

17:31.132 --> 17:33.301
What is going on here?

17:33.301 --> 17:34.552
[ Sighs ]

17:34.552 --> 17:36.304
Okay, this has gone on
long enough.

17:36.304 --> 17:38.431
I have to come clean.

17:41.226 --> 17:43.603
Bill hates plaid shirts.

17:43.603 --> 17:46.064
Jo hates the purse.

17:46.064 --> 17:47.565
Bill hates everything
you've ever given him!

17:47.565 --> 17:50.318
Jo ran over a possum!
[ Gasps ]

17:57.992 --> 18:00.495
So, you don't like
my presents?

18:02.163 --> 18:07.794
Mom, listen, w‐w‐we ‐‐
we appreciate them so much.

18:07.794 --> 18:10.547
But, yes, we hate them.

18:10.547 --> 18:13.216
Oh.

18:13.216 --> 18:16.636
Alright, I'll cool it
on the presents.

18:16.636 --> 18:19.472
That's it?

18:19.472 --> 18:21.516
Yeah, what did you think
was gonna happen?

18:21.516 --> 18:23.977
Nah, I knew you'd be
totally cool with it.

18:25.478 --> 18:27.647
Yeah, I'm cool.

18:27.647 --> 18:29.816
Okay,
so you're not mad?

18:29.816 --> 18:31.484
Why would I be mad?

18:31.484 --> 18:33.319
I‐I‐I‐I only
give you gifts

18:33.319 --> 18:34.529
because
I don't contribute.

18:34.529 --> 18:37.824
I don't pay rent.
I‐I don't buy groceries.

18:39.200 --> 18:42.495
Now I can stop.

18:42.495 --> 18:44.706
Okay, great.

18:44.706 --> 18:46.082
Thank you!
Bye!

18:46.082 --> 18:51.045
Bye, bye, bye, bye, bye, bye.
Bye. Bye. Bye.

18:54.632 --> 18:56.634
Feels like
we just got played again.

18:58.178 --> 19:00.638
You know what?
Who cares if she buys groceries.

19:00.638 --> 19:03.266
I can finally wear
Hawaiian shirts.

19:04.809 --> 19:07.645
Hawaiian shirts.

19:07.645 --> 19:09.481
And I can use
my old purse.

19:09.481 --> 19:11.816
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

19:11.816 --> 19:15.403
Emily: [ Singsong voice ]
Mom. Dad.

19:15.403 --> 19:18.156
And it feels like we're gonna
get played a third time.

19:18.156 --> 19:23.786
♪♪

19:23.786 --> 19:25.413
[ Normal voice ] Watch.

19:32.045 --> 19:34.214
[ Fan whirs ]

19:37.592 --> 19:38.635
Oh.

19:44.307 --> 19:46.893
I built the thing
from the iPad game.

19:46.893 --> 19:50.271
Emily,
this is amazing.

19:50.271 --> 19:53.107
I‐I am so proud of you.

19:53.107 --> 19:55.652
Wait. Hold on. Thi‐‐ This is why
you wanted the trophy?

19:56.486 --> 19:58.488
I should've just
given it to you.

19:58.488 --> 20:01.199
I know you don't like Lulu
better than me.

20:01.199 --> 20:04.118
I just said that 'cause I knew
you were gonna give me a trophy.

20:04.118 --> 20:06.120
And you did.

20:07.288 --> 20:11.376
You guys are a puzzle,
and I figured you out.

20:11.376 --> 20:15.129
[ Laughing maniacally ]

20:22.428 --> 20:24.430
Hey, babe.
Hm?

20:24.430 --> 20:26.015
What do you think,
the one with a lot of pineapples

20:26.015 --> 20:28.560
or the one with
all the hot sauces?

20:31.312 --> 20:32.605
[ Knock on door ]

20:32.605 --> 20:34.482
I'll get that.
You're very busy.

20:38.194 --> 20:39.904
[ Sighs ]

20:39.904 --> 20:41.073
Chuy.

20:41.073 --> 20:42.825
I've given this
a lot of thought,

20:42.825 --> 20:45.077
and some things are more
important than participation.

20:45.077 --> 20:47.246
One of them is family,
which is why I'm here ‐‐

20:47.246 --> 20:49.623
Chuy, stop talking.
It's all settled.

20:49.623 --> 20:50.749
It is?

20:50.749 --> 20:52.459
Yeah,
she just wanted the trophy

20:52.459 --> 20:56.171
for this, like, crazy,
cool machine thing.

20:56.171 --> 20:58.757
Ha‐ha!

21:01.302 --> 21:03.012
God is so funny.

21:04.680 --> 21:07.266
Here I am, about to compromise
everything I hold dear

21:07.266 --> 21:08.892
to make a child happy,

21:08.892 --> 21:10.144
and He shows me

21:10.144 --> 21:12.605
that rules are more important
than children.

21:13.522 --> 21:16.191
Have a great night!

21:17.610 --> 21:18.527
[ Door closes ]
